		"description": "<p>You combine rigorous magical academics with sincere devotion to a higher power, giving you a varied and potent mix of magicks to draw upon. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Intelligence or Wisdom score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with the Arcana and Religion skills, or an expertise die if you are already proficient. You also gain a skill specialty for each.</li>\n<li>You can use a cleric spellcasting focus with wizard spells and vice versa.</li>\n<li>If a spell appears on both the cleric and wizard lists for you, you add your cleric and wizard levels together to determine whether you can prepare the spell. Such a spell must be learned and prepared as a wizard spell (counting as usual against the class&rsquo;s prepared spells limit).&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>",
